<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-292-570  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 292 570.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The New York Times  March 31 1990 v139 p17(N) p31(L) 12 col in.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>U.S. easing on exports of computers.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wines, Michael.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The US Department of Defense (DOD) will no longer block sales ofvarious American-made mainframe computers to the Soviet Union andEastern Europe.andP;  Control of such exports will be left to the USDepartment of Commerce.andP;  This announcement covers low-endmainframes such as IBM's 3031, 4331 and 4341 machines.andP;  The USalready has agreed to end export controls on microcomputers among17 nations in the Coordinating Committee on Multilateral ExportControls (COCOM).andP;  Commerce Secretary Robert A. Mosbacher saysthat the Pentagon's decision 'reflects the Administration'sunderstanding of changing circumstances in East-West relations.'andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer industryInternational TradeUnited StatesUnited States. Department of CommerceSoviet UnionEastern EuropeCoordinating Committee for Multilateral Export Controls.andO;Person:    Mosbacher, Robert A. (commercial policy).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>